06/06/2007
VUKOVAR, Croatia -- Police said on Tuesday (June 5th) that they detained six Croatian Serbs on war crimes charges.
The deputy head of the local police department, Miroslav Janic, describes the men as former members of a Serb paramilitary formation, suspected of committing atrocities against Croatian soldiers and civilians in the Vukovar settlement of Luzac in November 1991.
One suspect is currently a policeman.
Three other suspects are being sought.
(HRT, RTS - 05/06/07)
